text: Pichaqa (Aymara pichaqa, phichaqa, piqacha a big needle, see: Piqacha, pichaqa and Phichaqa also spelled Pichaka) is a mountain in the Andes of Bolivia. It is situated in the La Paz Department, Pacajes Province, Calacoto Municipality. Pichaqa lies north-east of the Anallajsi volcano. == References == Category:Mountains of La Paz Department (Bolivia)
title: Pichaqa
